HEADWORD: Alpinia
<hw>Alpinia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>a genus of
perennial rhizomatous herbs of Asia and Australia and Polynesia having
ginger-scented rhizomes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Alpinia</gen>, genus <gen>Zerumbet</gen>,
genus <gen>Languas</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
